      "content": "Combining melatonin and Ambien is definitely boosting your odds of sleeping, but you need to be strategic about timing. Since Ambien is the main sedative, start taking it exactly as prescribed first, perhaps only adding melatonin an hour *before* Ambien. Never increase dosages based on your own hunch; it's best to maintain the prescribed regimen while noting if your sleep quality truly improves. If you're restless, definitely take a quick dose of your doctor-recommended melatonin alongside your usual evening routine.",
